It also discusses the complexity class NP, which falls under computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of shadows and lifts is a common technique in graph theory and combinatorics, which are also covered in the categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper discusses the characterization of coloring problems, which is related to logic and set theory (cs.LO).
